  "author_association": "NONE",
  "body": "@kargakis @nikhiljindal @ironcladlou @davidopp \n\nCurrent, deployment has no cleanup policy, old rc will always be preserved, I propose to add a `CleanupPolicy` field to `DeploymentSpec` indicating delete/preserve/remove the old rc. Just like `kubectl rollingupdate` does.\n\n``` go\ntype DeploymentSpec struct {\n    /*\n    ...\n    */\n    CleanupPolicy DeploymentCleanupPolicy\n}\n\ntype DeploymentCleanupPolicy string\n\nconst(\n// DeleteDeploymentCleanupPolicy means delete the old controller.\n    DeleteDeploymentCleanupPolicy DeploymentCleanupPolicy = \"Delete\"\n// PreserveDeploymentCleanupPolicy means keep the old controller.\n// if user not set DeploymentCleanupPolicy, this will be the default\n    PreserveDeploymentCleanupPolicy DeploymentCleanupPolicy = \"Preserve\"\n// RenameDeploymentCleanupPolicy means delete the old controller, and rename\n// the new controller to the name of the old controller.\n    RenameDeploymentCleanupPolicy DeploymentCleanupPolicy = \"Rename\"\n)\n```\n\nI will send a PR to address this if it looks good.\n",
